Poll: Former prez would be an asset to Sen. Clinton in White House

WASHINGTON (CNN) -- A majority of Americans think former President Bill Clinton would be an asset to Sen. Hillary
Clinton, D-New York, should she win the race for the White House, according to a new CNN/Opinion Research Corporation
Poll.

If Sen. Clinton wins the Democratic presidential nomination and goes on to win the general election in 2008, 60 percent
of Americans believe her husband would have a positive effect on her administration, while 30 percent think it would be
negative. President Clinton served two terms as commander-in-chief.

--CNN's Lauren Kornreich

